    {
      "id": "200.1.04",
      "q": "Select the statement that is most correct.",
      "options": [
        "The dorsal root ganglion is a motor-only structure",
        "The cell bodies of afferent ganglia are located in the spinal cord",
        "Ganglia associated with afferent nerve fibers contain cell bodies of sensory neurons",
        "Ganglia are collections of neuron cell bodies in the spinal cord that are associated with efferent fibers"
      ],
      "answer": 2,
      "explain": "Advance into this: And let me show you the terminology. Ganglia are clusters of neuron cell bodies located OUTSIDE the CNS. The dorsal root ganglia contain the cell bodies of sensory neurons — the command centers for incoming signals. Inside the CNS, similar clusters are called nuclei. Here's the delicious distinction: Same structure, different neighborhood, different name. The terminology matters. It reveals location.",
      "mechanism": {
        "title": "Ganglia vs. Nuclei: Where Cell Bodies Live",
        "content": "Let me take you through the fundamental anatomical distinction, and Carry this forward — this is beautiful. Collections of neuron cell bodies OUTSIDE the CNS are ganglia; those INSIDE the CNS are nuclei. Now See what happens next: Categories unfold: SENSORY GANGLIA — Dorsal root ganglia contain pseudounipolar sensory neuron cell bodies. These neurons sit OUTSIDE the spinal cord, in the intervertebral foramen. One branch extends to the periphery (to detect stimuli), the other extends into the dorsal horn (to transmit signals). The crescendo approaches: The signal doesn't have to cross a synapse in the ganglion — it flows through the cell body without stopping. Fast sensory transmission. AUTONOMIC GANGLIA — Sympathetic chain ganglia, collateral ganglia, and terminal ganglia contain motor neuron cell bodies for the autonomic nervous system. MOTOR NUCLEI — Motor neuron cell bodies for skeletal muscles are located in the ventral horn of the spinal cord — inside the CNS, so they're nuclei, not ganglia. Allow this to wash over you: : Location defines terminology. Geography is taxonomy.",
        "metaphor": "Sustain this attention: And I'll show you the corporate structure. Ganglia are like satellite offices — clusters of workers located out in the field, away from headquarters (CNS). They handle local operations and relay information back to central command. Nuclei are departments within headquarters itself, coordinating operations from inside the building. Same function, different location, different organizational name."
      },
      "isotopes": [
        "ans.structure"
      ],
